Blur your top layer by going to "Filters > Blur > Gaussian Blur" in the Gimp menu.

you have a total of 4 layers, the top 3 layers all in burn mode!
Invert the colors of your top layer by going to "Colors > Invert" in the Gimp menu.
Try the following layer blending modes for your top layer for differet 'alien' looks:
Color - this will make your skin a blue like the Avatar aliens.

resolution - a measure of the quality of a digital image. The more pixels a
an image has, the higher-quality the image will appear when you zoom out
mask - a mask is a shape or form that you apply to an image to allow you to
hide some parts of the image, and show others
opacity - how transparent / see-through vs. how opaque an image is.
Instructions based on GNU Image Manipulation Program version 2.8
GIMP can be downloaded for free for any computer system from www.gimp.org
